1
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:53,471
I actually look a lot like Lim Hyeon-jun.

2
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:54,889
-Really?
-Yes, totally.

3
00:00:54,972 --> 00:00:57,308
-Want to check for yourself?
-If you schedule a transaction on Onion,

4
00:00:57,391 --> 00:00:59,268
you can talk on the app for 30 minutes.

5
00:01:00,269 --> 00:01:01,187
I guess I'll find out.

6
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:02,271
How about this Friday?

7
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:03,314
At 10:30 p.m.

8
00:01:28,672 --> 00:01:29,507
Ms. Wi.

9
00:01:30,883 --> 00:01:32,635
Ms. Wi, wake up.

10
00:01:32,718 --> 00:01:33,677
Ms. Wi, are you okay?

11
00:01:34,553 --> 00:01:36,597
If it's too much, do you want to go home?

12
00:01:46,565 --> 00:01:48,818
I deliberately released that article,
you know.

13
00:01:51,612 --> 00:01:52,613
Why?

14
00:01:52,696 --> 00:01:54,615
My mother never did anything wrong to you.

15
00:01:54,698 --> 00:01:56,033
-So will you fire me?
-Should I?

16
00:01:56,617 --> 00:01:58,702
If you can't stand me, go ahead.
What's stopping you?

17
00:01:59,411 --> 00:02:01,622
Because you mean nothing to me anymore.

18
00:02:01,705 --> 00:02:04,375
You're being overly friendly
to Wi Jeong-sin.

19
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:09,755
When did you become so dense?

20
00:02:09,839 --> 00:02:12,675
There's only one reason
a man is friendly to a woman,

21
00:02:13,884 --> 00:02:15,135
isn't there?

22
00:02:18,681 --> 00:02:19,723
Can I go now?

23
00:02:22,768 --> 00:02:24,979
If you're putting on a show for me,
I've seen enough.

24
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:32,319
Don't tell me you're jealous.

25
00:02:48,252 --> 00:02:50,212
What are you doing?
Have you lost your mind?

26
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:51,964
Cut me some slack.

27
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,425
You know what today is.

28
00:02:55,217 --> 00:02:56,719
Consider that your birthday gift to me.

29
00:03:09,273 --> 00:03:13,152
I have called this press conference

30
00:03:13,611 --> 00:03:15,613
to address the dating rumors
involving a female doctor.

31
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:20,534
The person identified as my partner
in an exclusive report

32
00:03:20,618 --> 00:03:22,703
is actually my biological daughter.

33
00:03:28,334 --> 00:03:29,293
The taxi's here.

34
00:03:30,377 --> 00:03:32,588
Here we go. Watch your head.

35
00:03:34,173 --> 00:03:37,468
I live in the same direction as Ms. Wi,
so I can drop her off on my way.

36
00:03:37,551 --> 00:03:39,053
Okay. I'll text you her address.

37
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:41,639
-All right. Have a good night.
-Goodbye!

38
00:03:44,058 --> 00:03:46,310
-Come on.
-No, I can't.

39
00:03:48,187 --> 00:03:49,813
I should head home now.

40
00:03:50,856 --> 00:03:51,982
You're drunk. Go home.

41
00:03:54,818 --> 00:03:56,820
Okay, here we go.

42
00:04:06,455 --> 00:04:10,209
Regarding Sports Eunseong,
the media outlet behind the article,

43
00:04:10,292 --> 00:04:11,961
and Reporter Wi Jeong-sin,

44
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:15,464
I will be suing them for defamation.

45
00:04:44,410 --> 00:04:46,036
MELOMASTER (ONION FRIEND)

46
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:54,920
Are you okay?

47
00:04:55,004 --> 00:04:56,463
Are you…

48
00:04:59,883 --> 00:05:02,594
MELOMASTER (ONION FRIEND)

49
00:05:04,388 --> 00:05:06,181
You have a phone call.

50
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:12,980
Hello?

51
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:15,274
SOULISHERE (ONION FRIEND)

52
00:05:15,357 --> 00:05:16,400
Hello?

53
00:05:17,443 --> 00:05:18,694
Is anyone there?

54
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:22,906
Hello?

55
00:05:30,873 --> 00:05:31,707
Who was that?

56
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:32,708
Was that her boyfriend?

57
00:05:36,879 --> 00:05:37,713
Is she married?

58
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:46,805
Somebody from work is calling.

59
00:05:52,936 --> 00:05:55,647
This is Reporter Wi Jeong-sin's phone.

60
00:05:56,648 --> 00:05:58,275
Ms. Wi isn't quite…

61
00:06:02,571 --> 00:06:03,822
Wait, that's…

62
00:06:07,117 --> 00:06:09,328
Hello, this is Wi Jeong-sin speaking.

63
00:06:09,411 --> 00:06:12,456
Hey, it's total chaos at work.
You need to get here now.

64
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:14,458
Huh? What did you say?

65
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:19,129
Excuse me, sir.

66
00:06:19,213 --> 00:06:20,881
Could you drop me off at Sports Eunseong?

67
00:06:20,964 --> 00:06:21,799
Yes, ma'am.

68
00:06:22,591 --> 00:06:23,759
Why?

69
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:25,385
What's the matter?

70
00:06:26,136 --> 00:06:29,223
I think I'm needed back in the office.

71
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:32,017
But why are you here?

72
00:06:32,101 --> 00:06:35,854
A post on an online forum
has sparked a heated debate

73
00:06:35,938 --> 00:06:38,607
after a man claimed to be
unfairly accused of an affair.

74
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:41,777
The man claims he chatted online
with a woman he met on social media

75
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:44,238
without knowing she was married.

76
00:06:44,321 --> 00:06:46,156
When the husband found out,

77
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,534
he filed a lawsuit against the man
for having an affair with his wife.

78
00:06:48,617 --> 00:06:51,829
The man insists he never had
any physical contact with the woman,

79
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:55,332
-and maintains his innocence.
-I swear I'm innocent. Me, an adulterer?

80
00:06:55,415 --> 00:06:57,793
I can't believe I'm getting sued for this.

81
00:06:57,876 --> 00:07:00,504
There was absolutely no physical contact.

82
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:02,548
We've never even spoken on the phone.

83
00:07:02,631 --> 00:07:04,258
This is so unfair!

84
00:07:07,344 --> 00:07:09,096
-Jeez.
-We have breaking news in entertainment.

85
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:12,599
Actor Yoon Jung-ho held
an emergency press conference tonight

86
00:07:12,683 --> 00:07:16,937
to issue a statement on dating rumors
involving a female doctor in her 40s,

87
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:19,398
which is drawing much attention
from the public.

88
00:07:19,481 --> 00:07:21,108
Let's take a look at the press conference.

89
00:07:21,191 --> 00:07:22,526
She's not my romantic partner.

90
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:24,611
REVEALED TO BE HIS DAUGHTER,
NOT A ROMANTIC PARTNER

91
00:07:24,695 --> 00:07:26,655
She's my biological daughter.

92
00:07:26,738 --> 00:07:29,867
-Oh, gosh.
-She was born from an extramarital affair

93
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,451
during my second marriage.

94
00:07:31,535 --> 00:07:33,704
I fell short of what's expected
from a public figure,

95
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:37,249
and I apologize
for keeping her hidden for so long.

96
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:39,084
EPISODE 7

97
00:07:43,422 --> 00:07:44,256
What happened?

98
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:47,176
She's his daughter, not his lover.

99
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:48,844
It's like a soap opera.

100
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:49,887
Wi Jeong-sin.

101
00:07:54,683 --> 00:07:58,520
Do you still consider yourself
the Korean Journalist of the Year winner?

102
00:07:58,604 --> 00:08:00,480
-Excuse me?
-Take care of this yourself.

103
00:08:00,564 --> 00:08:02,149
It's too humiliating for the company,

104
00:08:02,232 --> 00:08:05,068
so do whatever it takes,
whether you beg or blackmail him.

105
00:08:05,152 --> 00:08:07,070
He sent the lawsuit by express courier.

106
00:08:07,154 --> 00:08:09,573
If he doesn't drop the lawsuit,
don't even think of coming in.

107
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:20,709
COMPLAINT

108
00:08:34,223 --> 00:08:35,265
Man, I'm exhausted.

109
00:08:36,225 --> 00:08:38,810
Oh, is my little boy up?

110
00:08:38,894 --> 00:08:41,563
Mommy had to return to the office
because something came up.

111
00:08:41,647 --> 00:08:45,817
I'll be home soon,
so you go back to sleep, okay?

112
00:08:45,901 --> 00:08:47,277
I love you, my sweet boy.

113
00:08:47,361 --> 00:08:50,072
Give Mommy a kiss.

114
00:09:04,127 --> 00:09:05,295
Oh, excuse me.

115
00:09:09,466 --> 00:09:10,676
Have you sobered up?

116
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:11,760
Yes.

117
00:09:12,261 --> 00:09:13,845
Does the chief have a son?

118
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:16,431
You didn't know?
She's divorced and has a kid.

119
00:09:16,515 --> 00:09:17,349
She is?

120
00:09:18,642 --> 00:09:21,353
But nobody knows who the father is.

121
00:09:21,937 --> 00:09:22,938
It's a mystery.

122
00:09:25,148 --> 00:09:28,485
-She's a troll posing as a reporter.
-Who knew I'd memorize a reporter's name?

123
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,612
Jeez, what a mess.

124
00:09:30,696 --> 00:09:33,407
The true problem with the media
is the reporters.

125
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:34,741
This is insane.

126
00:09:35,284 --> 00:09:37,577
If she deserved
the Korean Journalist of the Year award,

127
00:09:37,661 --> 00:09:39,079
I deserve the Nobel Peace Prize.

128
00:09:39,162 --> 00:09:41,665
Jeez, I knew this would happen.

129
00:09:41,748 --> 00:09:43,792
She flat-out acted like the paparazzi,

130
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:46,503
-so what's she going to do now?
-My uncle works at Eunseongilbo

131
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,505
-and says she was a political reporter.
-Where are all the trolls

132
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:50,048
who posted "senile" hate comments?

133
00:09:51,425 --> 00:09:52,509
Seriously.

134
00:09:55,053 --> 00:09:57,389
REPORTER WI JEONG-SIN

135
00:09:57,973 --> 00:09:58,807
Wait.

136
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:01,059
What does this even have to do with me?

137
00:10:01,143 --> 00:10:02,519
She can take care of herself.

138
00:10:08,358 --> 00:10:09,901
But can she?

139
00:10:16,575 --> 00:10:17,826
IS WI JEONG-SIN EVEN A REAL REPORTER?

140
00:10:17,909 --> 00:10:21,330
You got about 5,000 hate comments
on UTube and on social media.

141
00:10:21,413 --> 00:10:24,041
I guess what doesn't kill you
makes you stronger.

142
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:26,001
Do you see a resemblance?

143
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:29,212
Not really. Why?

144
00:10:29,963 --> 00:10:31,882
-Is their relationship a lie?
-It's possible.

145
00:10:31,965 --> 00:10:34,134
Maybe he's in a situation
where he needs to avoid scandals.

146
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:35,635
Like what?

147
00:10:37,596 --> 00:10:39,514
The National Assembly
candidate selection is coming up.

148
00:10:40,265 --> 00:10:43,143
They say Yoon Jung-ho secured
the ruling party's nod for Mucheon City.

149
00:10:43,226 --> 00:10:45,729
He also openly talked about
wanting to go into politics.

150
00:10:46,521 --> 00:10:49,649
During last year's presidential election,
he often showed up at campaign events.

151
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:52,027
Look at you.

152
00:10:53,487 --> 00:10:54,571
That sounds plausible.

153
00:10:58,575 --> 00:10:59,534
Who is it?

154
00:10:59,618 --> 00:11:01,870
I'm Reporter Wi Jeong-sin
from Sports Eunseong.

155
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:03,789
Is Mr. Yoon Jung-ho at home?

156
00:11:29,898 --> 00:11:31,733
I can't say I'm happy to see you.

157
00:11:31,817 --> 00:11:34,319
I only let you in
because you waited all night.

158
00:11:34,403 --> 00:11:35,404
Thank you, sir.

159
00:11:35,487 --> 00:11:39,366
Once I make a decision,
I follow through, no matter what.

160
00:11:39,449 --> 00:11:42,160
So if you're here to beg me
to drop the lawsuit,

161
00:11:42,244 --> 00:11:43,662
you can be on your way.

162
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:45,914
-I'm not here to beg.
-What?

163
00:11:46,498 --> 00:11:47,833
I'm here to let you know

164
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,585
-that if you don't drop the lawsuit,
-What?

165
00:11:50,669 --> 00:11:53,255
you'll find yourself
in a very uncomfortable

166
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:55,340
and embarrassing situation
for a long time.

167
00:11:55,424 --> 00:11:56,633
What did you say?

168
00:11:57,801 --> 00:11:59,594
Why you disrespectful…

169
00:12:01,263 --> 00:12:04,391
Hey, is that all you have to say?

170
00:12:04,474 --> 00:12:05,559
Yes, it is.

171
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:09,146
That little…

172
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:10,814
Hey!

173
00:12:15,819 --> 00:12:17,821
More! Keep the pressure on!

174
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:19,948
That's it! You're doing great.

175
00:12:20,031 --> 00:12:21,032
Move in again.

176
00:12:23,118 --> 00:12:24,453
Keep your guard up!

177
00:12:24,536 --> 00:12:26,621
Block him! Look for an opening!

178
00:12:26,705 --> 00:12:29,249
Wait for your shot! Good!

179
00:12:30,959 --> 00:12:32,169
Keep your guard up.

180
00:12:36,298 --> 00:12:38,341
-Are you okay?
-Let's take a break.

181
00:12:44,514 --> 00:12:45,557
SOULISHERE

182
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:47,934
Hello? Is anyone there?

183
00:12:55,775 --> 00:12:56,651
Onion!

184
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:07,204
Some guy answered your phone last night.

185
00:13:08,497 --> 00:13:11,374
-Is everything okay?
-Oh, man.

186
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:12,792
I'm sorry.

187
00:13:12,876 --> 00:13:15,712
I drank too much at the team dinner
and fell asleep in the taxi.

188
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:18,882
My boss was with me,
and I think he answered my phone.

189
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:21,343
Right, of course.

190
00:13:22,677 --> 00:13:24,346
For a second there,

191
00:13:24,429 --> 00:13:28,099
I thought it was
your husband or boyfriend.

192
00:13:35,357 --> 00:13:36,525
AN APPOINTMENT HAS BEEN BOOKED
"VIEW APPOINTMENT"

193
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:40,737
"An appointment has been booked"?

194
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:45,700
SOULISHERE (ONION FRIEND)

195
00:13:46,409 --> 00:13:47,410
Wait, this…

196
00:13:51,915 --> 00:13:52,749
What do I…

197
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:01,675
Hello?

198
00:14:03,718 --> 00:14:05,053
I'm not married.

199
00:14:07,639 --> 00:14:09,182
Right.

200
00:14:09,266 --> 00:14:10,850
I guess that's a relief, then.

201
00:14:14,604 --> 00:14:18,066
Anyway, it sounds like you're close

202
00:14:18,984 --> 00:14:20,151
with your male boss.

203
00:14:21,319 --> 00:14:23,780
Well, we're not close.

204
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:26,324
We only shared a taxi since we were
headed in the same direction.

205
00:14:26,992 --> 00:14:29,536
Oh, I see.

206
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:31,663
I'm sorry I misunderstood you.

207
00:14:32,622 --> 00:14:33,582
Also,

208
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:35,792
thank you…

209
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:37,752
for calling.

210
00:14:43,675 --> 00:14:44,551
Gosh.

211
00:14:45,677 --> 00:14:47,637
It's nice to hear your voice.

212
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:51,766
I feel the same.

213
00:14:52,475 --> 00:14:53,602
By the way,

214
00:14:53,685 --> 00:14:56,688
you really do sound
exactly like Lim Hyeon-jun.

215
00:14:56,771 --> 00:14:58,273
See, I told you!

216
00:14:58,815 --> 00:15:00,400
I told you I sound exactly like him.

217
00:15:00,483 --> 00:15:04,237
Can you say a line from Kang Pil-gu?

218
00:15:04,321 --> 00:15:05,155
Sorry?

219
00:15:07,282 --> 00:15:08,116
Oh, sure.

220
00:15:12,621 --> 00:15:14,706
"They say you can't fix people."

221
00:15:15,290 --> 00:15:17,125
"But I do."

222
00:15:20,879 --> 00:15:23,632
Wow, how are you so good at impressions?

223
00:15:23,715 --> 00:15:25,050
Impressions…

224
00:15:27,802 --> 00:15:29,304
My gosh, you sounded just like him.

225
00:15:29,971 --> 00:15:31,514
Hey, come and eat.

226
00:15:33,391 --> 00:15:36,269
I have to get ready for work,
so I need to hang up.

227
00:15:36,353 --> 00:15:37,520
Oh, I see.

228
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:39,773
Then,

229
00:15:40,357 --> 00:15:42,442
we'll talk soon.

230
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:43,401
Right.

231
00:15:43,485 --> 00:15:44,569
Okay.

232
00:15:47,197 --> 00:15:48,031
What the heck?

233
00:15:52,118 --> 00:15:53,161
Jeez.

234
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:56,414
What am I doing?

235
00:15:57,749 --> 00:15:58,875
Gosh.

236
00:16:06,549 --> 00:16:08,468
Let's go again. Nice.

237
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:10,637
Be precise. That's it!

238
00:16:12,931 --> 00:16:14,265
Nice!

239
00:16:14,891 --> 00:16:16,476
Yes, keep going!

240
00:16:20,271 --> 00:16:21,231
One more time!

241
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:23,483
That's it! Good job!

242
00:16:28,113 --> 00:16:30,365
Do we need to check if he's on something?

243
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:32,409
Seriously, what's gotten into him?

244
00:16:37,622 --> 00:16:38,998
How long will you keep that up?

245
00:16:43,586 --> 00:16:44,629
Talk to me.

246
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:46,840
What is it?

247
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:51,970
I'm asking nicely.
Don't make me beat it out of you.

248
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:54,013
I'm counting to three.

249
00:16:54,097 --> 00:16:56,516
-One, two, three!
-The audition.

250
00:16:56,599 --> 00:16:58,226
I failed the audition.

251
00:16:58,768 --> 00:16:59,936
What?

252
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:01,104
Hey, come on.

253
00:17:02,397 --> 00:17:04,733
It's not the first time
you failed an audition.

254
00:17:05,316 --> 00:17:06,943
This is all your fault!

255
00:17:07,652 --> 00:17:10,029
Even I would flunk
the brother of someone I can't stand.

256
00:17:11,072 --> 00:17:12,949
What are you talking about?

257
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:14,784
At the audition,

258
00:17:14,868 --> 00:17:17,245
my bro Kang Pil-gu himself failed me.

259
00:17:17,328 --> 00:17:20,039
He gave me an earful too,
like he had a lot bottled up inside.

260
00:17:20,957 --> 00:17:22,041
I get it now.

261
00:17:22,125 --> 00:17:24,294
Are you here for revenge?

262
00:17:24,377 --> 00:17:27,756
Now do you understand how awful it feels
when your family gets dragged?

263
00:17:31,259 --> 00:17:32,218
Damn it.

264
00:17:34,262 --> 00:17:35,889
Is Ms. Wi coming in today?

265
00:17:35,972 --> 00:17:38,433
I assume she will.
She needs to clear out her desk.

266
00:17:38,516 --> 00:17:41,269
Jeez, and we already gave her
a farewell party.

267
00:17:43,021 --> 00:17:44,105
Hello.

268
00:17:44,189 --> 00:17:45,690
-You're here.
-Hi.

269
00:17:51,529 --> 00:17:53,782
Okay, we've got a lot of interviews today.

270
00:17:53,865 --> 00:17:55,033
Right.

271
00:17:55,617 --> 00:17:56,785
Hello, sir.

272
00:17:58,578 --> 00:17:59,704
-Hello.
-Hello, Mr. Lee.

273
00:18:05,919 --> 00:18:06,795
He's so cool.

274
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:12,592
I think something's going on
between Mr. Lee and our chief.

275
00:18:12,675 --> 00:18:13,510
Seriously?

276
00:18:13,593 --> 00:18:16,721
The night of Jeong-sin's farewell party,

277
00:18:16,805 --> 00:18:19,224
I was coming out of the restroom
and saw them kissing!

278
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:21,601
-Holy cow.
-Are you serious?

279
00:18:21,684 --> 00:18:22,560
Yes!

280
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,146
Maybe you saw it wrong.

281
00:18:25,897 --> 00:18:27,565
Right, what if you saw it wrong?

282
00:18:27,649 --> 00:18:30,109
Hey, I have 20/20 vision.

283
00:18:31,778 --> 00:18:33,905
Wow, Mr. Lee's such a man.

284
00:18:33,988 --> 00:18:34,864
Nope.

285
00:18:35,824 --> 00:18:36,950
The chief kissed him first.

286
00:18:37,492 --> 00:18:38,868
-What?
-No way.

287
00:18:42,247 --> 00:18:43,331
Here you are.

288
00:18:44,207 --> 00:18:45,416
The chief editor is looking for you.

289
00:18:47,544 --> 00:18:48,878
My transfer's been canceled?

290
00:18:48,962 --> 00:18:52,298
Did you really think the political desk
would welcome you back after this fiasco?

291
00:18:54,175 --> 00:18:56,261
Take a few days off
and come back when things cool down.

292
00:18:56,344 --> 00:18:58,304
But his claim hasn't even been verified.

293
00:18:58,388 --> 00:19:00,682
He's talking about genetic testing,
but it can't be legally enforced!

294
00:19:00,765 --> 00:19:02,892
It's obvious he'll keep putting it off
until it never happens!

295
00:19:02,976 --> 00:19:05,395
Also, he got the party nomination
and might run in the by-election--

296
00:19:05,478 --> 00:19:06,646
Here.

297
00:19:06,729 --> 00:19:07,689
Read it.

298
00:19:13,945 --> 00:19:15,154
GENETIC TEST REPORT

299
00:19:17,782 --> 00:19:19,117
PROBABILITY OF PATERNITY: 99.999%

300
00:19:20,368 --> 00:19:21,661
I have to issue a correction?

301
00:19:21,744 --> 00:19:24,122
Do you expect me to issue a correction
for an article you wrote?

302
00:19:24,706 --> 00:19:26,457
We have to issue a correction first

303
00:19:26,541 --> 00:19:27,834
before he drops the lawsuit.

304
00:19:43,099 --> 00:19:43,933
Ms. Wi.

305
00:19:48,104 --> 00:19:48,938
Have you eaten yet?

306
00:19:49,522 --> 00:19:51,316
-No.
-Then let's go eat.

307
00:19:52,442 --> 00:19:54,068
Do I look like the starving type?

308
00:19:55,194 --> 00:19:57,739
You keep vanishing
every time I invite you to eat.

309
00:19:58,698 --> 00:20:00,617
Promise that you'll eat with me today.

310
00:20:04,662 --> 00:20:06,497
Co-produce Kang Pil-gu?

311
00:20:06,581 --> 00:20:07,916
You're going into producing, Mr. Hwang?

312
00:20:10,293 --> 00:20:11,377
Yes, well…

313
00:20:11,961 --> 00:20:15,757
I thought I'd start out with this project.

314
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:20,470
I guess it's trendy for agencies
to get into production.

315
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:24,724
Well, actors don't just want to sit around
and wait for offers to come in.

316
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:28,603
They feel an urge to make something
on their own every now and then.

317
00:20:30,188 --> 00:20:32,148
This isn't a decision
I can make on my own.

318
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:34,192
I'll talk it over with my company.

319
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:35,318
Right.

320
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:39,197
And about Director Bak…

321
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:40,782
-Director Bak Byeong-gi?
-Yes.

322
00:20:42,575 --> 00:20:43,618
Gosh…

323
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:45,787
Go ahead and say it.

324
00:20:45,870 --> 00:20:47,288
-Well…
-Go ahead.

325
00:20:47,372 --> 00:20:49,374
You see, Director Bak used to be

326
00:20:49,457 --> 00:20:54,295
a very promising young director,

327
00:20:54,379 --> 00:20:56,923
but he hasn't directed in so long…

328
00:20:57,006 --> 00:21:00,051
-That's not true.
-That's an excellent point.

329
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:04,931
Director Bak is the genius type, so it…

330
00:21:05,014 --> 00:21:07,225
So unlike the previous seasons,

331
00:21:07,308 --> 00:21:10,436
it's possible this season
could turn out to be very…

332
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:12,522
Bak Byeong-gi is a total lunatic.

333
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:14,190
So we make one wrong move,

334
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:17,068
and it might turn out downright bizarre.

335
00:21:17,151 --> 00:21:18,194
Is that okay with you?

336
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:21,406
There's such a big difference in length
between movies and dramas,

337
00:21:21,489 --> 00:21:23,533
it could take him time to adjust to it.

338
00:21:23,616 --> 00:21:26,953
He films all day and night
in the name of art,

339
00:21:27,036 --> 00:21:29,122
so he'll go over
the time and budget limit.

340
00:21:29,205 --> 00:21:33,167
You'll need to do a really good job
putting together a key crew.

341
00:21:33,251 --> 00:21:35,712
The second unit director, gaffer,
director of photography, music director…

342
00:21:35,795 --> 00:21:38,214
I'm going to assign them myself.

343
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:39,132
End of discussion.

344
00:21:40,216 --> 00:21:43,177
I mean, I still trust he'll do a good job,

345
00:21:43,261 --> 00:21:46,431
but I'm a little concerned.

346
00:21:51,144 --> 00:21:52,437
Come on, bro.

347
00:21:53,521 --> 00:21:55,940
Is it really our place
to assign the key crew?

348
00:21:56,024 --> 00:21:58,901
I'm not assigning anyone.
I'm merely suggesting.

349
00:21:58,985 --> 00:22:00,194
Oh, so you're suggesting.

350
00:22:00,278 --> 00:22:01,738
You watched The Days of Romance.

351
00:22:01,821 --> 00:22:05,324
Cinematographer Hwang Ji-hyeok
is amazing at shooting male actors.

352
00:22:05,408 --> 00:22:06,784
That was a melodrama.

353
00:22:06,868 --> 00:22:08,369
This is a detective action series.

354
00:22:08,453 --> 00:22:11,622
It's not important
that your face looks soft and dreamy.

355
00:22:13,541 --> 00:22:14,500
It's good, right?

356
00:22:16,377 --> 00:22:17,211
What is it?

357
00:22:19,047 --> 00:22:20,214
It's important to me.

358
00:22:20,298 --> 00:22:21,632
I'm determined to do a melodrama next.

359
00:22:22,216 --> 00:22:23,801
Fine. How about a round
at a golf simulator?

360
00:22:24,886 --> 00:22:26,637
I have an appointment with Byeong-gi.

361
00:22:28,014 --> 00:22:29,599
Why are you meeting with him?

362
00:22:30,391 --> 00:22:32,310
Why? Tell me.

363
00:22:32,894 --> 00:22:33,728
You must be upset

364
00:22:34,604 --> 00:22:36,189
about not returning to the political desk.

365
00:22:39,025 --> 00:22:40,234
I suppose so.

366
00:22:40,318 --> 00:22:43,654
The public reacted so badly
to the Yoon Jung-ho article

367
00:22:44,322 --> 00:22:45,865
that I couldn't do anything about it.

368
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:50,495
But I have to say,

369
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:52,163
I can't help feeling excited.

370
00:22:53,998 --> 00:22:55,333
I get to keep seeing you like this

371
00:22:55,416 --> 00:22:56,709
since you're not returning
to the political desk.

372
00:23:02,131 --> 00:23:03,216
ERADICATING DIGITAL SEX CRIMES

373
00:23:05,718 --> 00:23:07,053
SIMPLE AND EASY, TAILORED FIT!

374
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:22,193
Are you a fan of Lim Hyeon-jun?

375
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:24,654
No.

376
00:23:26,489 --> 00:23:28,699
