377
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:30,952
And at the baseball stadium too.

378
00:23:32,745 --> 00:23:35,164
Oh, did I? I don't remember.

379
00:23:37,291 --> 00:23:38,584
Hey, slow down.

380
00:23:41,212 --> 00:23:42,213
This is good.

381
00:23:42,296 --> 00:23:43,214
Yes, it is.

382
00:23:46,217 --> 00:23:48,511
When I said I felt excited earlier,

383
00:23:48,594 --> 00:23:49,637
you know I was joking, right?

384
00:23:52,056 --> 00:23:54,016
Seeing you having to stick around
because of the incident

385
00:23:55,393 --> 00:23:56,519
doesn't make me feel good.

386
00:23:58,104 --> 00:23:58,980
Because of me?

387
00:23:59,981 --> 00:24:00,815
Yes.

388
00:24:05,695 --> 00:24:08,656
Do you always worry about
any woman you see?

389
00:24:10,658 --> 00:24:13,202
Well, I've always had good manners,

390
00:24:14,203 --> 00:24:15,288
but I'm not that easy.

391
00:24:16,831 --> 00:24:18,624
Are you aware that you confuse people?

392
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:22,295
I hear something's going on
between you and our chief.

393
00:24:23,171 --> 00:24:25,173
So let's not give anyone the wrong idea.

394
00:24:28,426 --> 00:24:30,845
I was in a relationship with her
a long time ago.

395
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:34,015
I don't know what you heard,

396
00:24:35,391 --> 00:24:36,267
but we're not together now.

397
00:24:37,810 --> 00:24:40,271
Are you feeling jealous?

398
00:24:42,773 --> 00:24:44,108
It's not like that.

399
00:25:05,213 --> 00:25:08,216
BAK BYEONG-GI

400
00:25:15,848 --> 00:25:17,475
-Come in.
-Thanks.

401
00:25:20,269 --> 00:25:21,854
This is nice.

402
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:24,232
When did you move to this studio?

403
00:25:24,899 --> 00:25:27,193
I needed a bigger place
because I have so many books.

404
00:25:27,276 --> 00:25:28,319
Would you like a beverage?

405
00:25:28,402 --> 00:25:29,737
-No.
-All right.

406
00:25:29,820 --> 00:25:32,240
Where's your assistant?
Why are you working alone?

407
00:25:32,323 --> 00:25:34,450
Everyone works from home these days.

408
00:25:36,035 --> 00:25:37,495
How much have you written so far?

409
00:25:38,079 --> 00:25:41,290
I sent in episodes five and six last week,
and now I'm writing seven and eight.

410
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:45,920
Once we have the supporting cast and crew,
we'll need to start filming right away.

411
00:25:46,003 --> 00:25:47,213
Will that be enough?

412
00:25:47,296 --> 00:25:49,757
You won't have time to write
because of the shoot preparations.

413
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:51,259
I'll have to make it happen.

414
00:25:54,595 --> 00:25:55,763
If you're having difficulty,

415
00:25:55,846 --> 00:25:58,140
how about getting a co-writer?

416
00:25:58,224 --> 00:25:59,058
A co-writer?

417
00:25:59,141 --> 00:26:00,017
Yeah.

418
00:26:00,518 --> 00:26:03,854
I can introduce you to someone
who's good at writing romantic lines.

419
00:26:04,605 --> 00:26:07,608
I've already mapped out the ending,
so it won't be hard to write the script.

420
00:26:07,692 --> 00:26:08,526
Don't worry about it.

421
00:26:13,614 --> 00:26:14,490
Oh, yeah?

422
00:26:15,741 --> 00:26:16,909
Well…

423
00:26:16,993 --> 00:26:19,161
I guess that's a relief.

424
00:26:20,997 --> 00:26:22,498
By the way,

425
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:26,377
the premise of Kang Pil-gu
becoming a corrupt detective…

426
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:28,838
Isn't that rather cliché?

427
00:26:30,298 --> 00:26:33,801
He takes part in a crime
to save his late colleague's sister.

428
00:26:33,884 --> 00:26:34,927
Do you not like it?

429
00:26:35,845 --> 00:26:39,015
You need to add something extra in there.

430
00:26:39,098 --> 00:26:40,224
Something extra?

431
00:26:43,686 --> 00:26:47,189
During the rescue sequence
of his colleague's kidnapped sister,

432
00:26:47,273 --> 00:26:48,691
how about…

433
00:26:48,774 --> 00:26:49,692
Mi-yeong!

434
00:26:55,489 --> 00:26:56,324
Mi-yeong.

435
00:26:58,993 --> 00:26:59,827
Mi-yeong.

436
00:27:06,584 --> 00:27:07,710
Cut!

437
00:27:08,502 --> 00:27:09,712
Bad take.

438
00:27:10,338 --> 00:27:11,505
Why?

439
00:27:13,424 --> 00:27:15,718
Is it a bit much?

440
00:27:23,184 --> 00:27:24,018
Out of the blue like that?

441
00:27:24,602 --> 00:27:26,562
Why would they French kiss
when they don't know each other?

442
00:27:26,645 --> 00:27:28,689
She's his colleague's sister,
and they're meeting for the first time.

443
00:27:28,773 --> 00:27:30,691
Then just set up a backstory.

444
00:27:30,775 --> 00:27:34,570
Maybe they were childhood friends,
or maybe Pil-gu saved her from drowning.

445
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:35,780
There are a ton of ideas.

446
00:27:35,863 --> 00:27:36,989
But why is that necessary?

447
00:27:37,073 --> 00:27:39,241
The viewers want to see Kang Pil-gu
in a romantic role.

448
00:27:42,453 --> 00:27:44,538
You refuse all romantic scenes
with the female lead,

449
00:27:44,622 --> 00:27:46,957
but it's fine with a minor character?
That makes no sense.

450
00:27:48,501 --> 00:27:50,753
A writer's job is to
make sense of such things.

451
00:27:51,253 --> 00:27:52,171
Are you freaking serious?

452
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:54,715
Did you just swear at me?

453
00:27:56,300 --> 00:27:58,052
I almost did, but no.

454
00:28:00,221 --> 00:28:02,640
I'll give it some thought.

455
00:28:03,516 --> 00:28:06,018
I'll think about how to add

456
00:28:07,353 --> 00:28:08,687
some romantic lines.

457
00:28:09,688 --> 00:28:10,898
Good.

458
00:28:10,981 --> 00:28:12,817
You're a good writer, Mr. Bak.

459
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:14,985
Give it your best shot, all right?

460
00:28:15,569 --> 00:28:18,072
-So, shall we go out and eat now?
-No, thank you.

461
00:28:18,614 --> 00:28:21,409
I have way too much to do.

462
00:28:21,492 --> 00:28:22,952
Enjoy your meal.

