00:33:37,099 --> 00:33:39,393
fail my brother at the audition
because of me?

526
00:33:40,936 --> 00:33:43,147
No, the thing is…

527
00:33:45,065 --> 00:33:47,735
Look, I don't let
petty emotions affect me.

528
00:33:47,818 --> 00:33:48,652
-The--
-If he couldn't act,

529
00:33:48,736 --> 00:33:49,903
you just had to fail him.

530
00:33:49,987 --> 00:33:51,405
Why did you have to rub salt in his wound?

531
00:33:51,488 --> 00:33:52,322
But that's not--

532
00:33:52,406 --> 00:33:54,825
Actors who go to auditions
are there to land a role,

533
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:56,744
not to receive guidance.

534
00:33:56,827 --> 00:33:58,412
Exactly, so that's why I--

535
00:33:58,495 --> 00:33:59,496
Goodbye, then.

536
00:34:07,921 --> 00:34:09,423
Oh, boy.

537
00:34:12,551 --> 00:34:14,845
Everything is so messed up.

538
00:34:29,902 --> 00:34:31,945
What in the world is she thinking?

539
00:34:32,654 --> 00:34:35,949
She was bumped from the political desk
to the entertainment desk.

540
00:34:36,033 --> 00:34:38,076
If she leaves the entertainment desk,
then what?

541
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:40,037
Where can she go?

542
00:35:03,685 --> 00:35:04,812
Damn it.

543
00:35:14,571 --> 00:35:15,781
Get in.

544
00:35:17,241 --> 00:35:19,117
Did you come out to give me a ride?

545
00:35:19,201 --> 00:35:21,078
No, I'm heading to the gym.

546
00:35:21,161 --> 00:35:22,746
Your home is on the way, so get in.

547
00:35:22,830 --> 00:35:24,540
You don't even know where I live.

548
00:35:24,623 --> 00:35:26,124
Are you refusing to get in, then?

549
00:35:44,685 --> 00:35:46,436
Stop wiping it down.

550
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:47,813
It's fine.

551
00:35:48,522 --> 00:35:50,858
You should've just hopped in right away.

552
00:35:52,651 --> 00:35:53,527
Thank you.

553
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:56,780
I know you're a busy man.
You should've just left.

554
00:35:58,156 --> 00:36:01,034
I knew you wouldn't have taken a taxi
or bought an umbrella.

555
00:36:01,118 --> 00:36:02,619
You would've just gotten soaked.

556
00:36:05,247 --> 00:36:06,123
How do you know?

557
00:36:07,541 --> 00:36:10,127
How do you know I wouldn't take a taxi
or buy an umbrella?

558
00:36:12,838 --> 00:36:14,715
I mean, it's obvious.

559
00:36:15,924 --> 00:36:16,925
You just look like the type.

560
00:36:21,722 --> 00:36:23,724
So how did you end up becoming a reporter?

561
00:36:24,266 --> 00:36:25,475
Why choose that over other jobs?

562
00:36:26,935 --> 00:36:28,270
It's a long story.

563
00:36:28,353 --> 00:36:29,521
Then make it short.

564
00:36:31,356 --> 00:36:35,527
Well, I had the looks,
but I also had the brains.

565
00:36:35,611 --> 00:36:38,113
I guess you could say
I was too perfect to be real.

566
00:36:38,196 --> 00:36:41,408
Gosh, I can't believe
your story begins with you showing off.

567
00:36:41,491 --> 00:36:42,576
Unbelievable.

568
00:36:42,659 --> 00:36:44,411
Go on. Continue.

569
00:36:45,495 --> 00:36:47,247
I was first in my class

570
00:36:47,915 --> 00:36:50,083
in elementary school,
middle school, and high school.

571
00:36:50,667 --> 00:36:51,793
But then…

572
00:36:51,877 --> 00:36:53,337
Second place?

573
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:57,007
I was shocked
because I'd never come in second before.

574
00:36:57,090 --> 00:36:59,718
And I couldn't help but suspect the kid
who suddenly took the top of the class,

575
00:36:59,801 --> 00:37:02,429
when he had never once
made it into the top 30.

576
00:37:02,930 --> 00:37:06,183
So from that day on,
I started keeping an eye on him.

577
00:37:30,457 --> 00:37:31,541
And that's when I knew

578
00:37:32,376 --> 00:37:33,877
how he came out on top.

579
00:37:33,961 --> 00:37:34,795
Wi Jeong-sin.

580
00:37:34,878 --> 00:37:37,255
When I told my teacher the truth,

581
00:37:37,339 --> 00:37:39,299
I naturally thought the problem
would be resolved.

582
00:37:40,717 --> 00:37:43,971
Knowing I didn't have parents
and lived alone with my brother,

583
00:37:44,054 --> 00:37:45,222
the school tried to coax me.

584
00:37:45,305 --> 00:37:47,307
The foundation
would pay my college tuition

585
00:37:47,391 --> 00:37:48,308
if I turned a blind eye.

586
00:37:48,392 --> 00:37:49,851
So what did you do?

587
00:37:49,935 --> 00:37:51,687
To be honest, I was tempted when they said

588
00:37:51,770 --> 00:37:53,063
they'd cover all my tuition.

589
00:37:53,730 --> 00:37:57,359
But seeing him shamelessly laugh
after stealing the answer key,

590
00:37:57,442 --> 00:37:59,403
and seeing the others laugh with him,

591
00:37:59,486 --> 00:38:01,697
not even aware
they were harmed by his actions,

592
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:03,323
made me snap out of it right away.

593
00:38:03,824 --> 00:38:05,701
So I reported it to the media.

594
00:38:05,784 --> 00:38:07,369
Oh, wow!

595
00:38:07,869 --> 00:38:09,204
What was really amazing was

596
00:38:09,287 --> 00:38:11,832
that it was resolved
the moment the coverage began.

597
00:38:11,915 --> 00:38:13,041
The Language Arts teacher got fired,

598
00:38:13,125 --> 00:38:15,460
and that kid was given a zero
and transferred out.

599
00:38:15,544 --> 00:38:17,504
It was a perfect case of karma.

600
00:38:17,587 --> 00:38:21,008
I got on the school's bad side
for damaging their reputation,

601
00:38:21,091 --> 00:38:24,511
but I got into Hankuk University
fair and square through the CSAT.

602
00:38:25,303 --> 00:38:26,847
That's my story.

603
00:38:26,930 --> 00:38:28,098
Wow.

604
00:38:28,598 --> 00:38:31,977
So that's why you became a reporter,
to punish the bad guys.

605
00:38:32,561 --> 00:38:35,397
By the way,
why do you keep driving in circles?

606
00:38:36,148 --> 00:38:38,734
We've driven across
every major bridge in Seoul.

607
00:38:39,776 --> 00:38:41,570
It's been a while since I've driven.

608
00:38:42,154 --> 00:38:43,530
All the roads look the same.

609
00:38:43,613 --> 00:38:45,365
But you said you knew the way.

610
00:38:46,116 --> 00:38:49,036
Your high school story was so interesting

611
00:38:49,119 --> 00:38:52,330
that I wanted to know how it ended,
and I took the long way.

612
00:38:52,914 --> 00:38:54,666
I'll get home before dawn, right?

613
00:38:54,750 --> 00:38:55,625
Before that,

614
00:38:57,044 --> 00:38:58,795
there's somewhere
you need to come with me.

615
00:39:00,714 --> 00:39:01,715
Why should I apologize?

616
00:39:01,798 --> 00:39:03,425
You need to apologize

617
00:39:04,051 --> 00:39:05,886
if you want him to drop the lawsuit!

618
00:39:05,969 --> 00:39:08,263
I'll hand in my resignation
before I apologize!

619
00:39:08,346 --> 00:39:09,181
Resignation?

620
00:39:09,264 --> 00:39:12,100
Standing by your principles
requires sacrifice.

621
00:39:12,184 --> 00:39:13,185
Don't be ridiculous.

622
00:39:13,268 --> 00:39:15,479
You're about to be fired
and summoned to court.

623
00:39:15,562 --> 00:39:16,980
Principles, my ass.

624
00:39:17,064 --> 00:39:18,899
Are you rich enough
that you don't need a job?

625
00:39:18,982 --> 00:39:21,860
You said you have no parents,
that it's just you and your brother.

626
00:39:21,943 --> 00:39:23,737
I get that. I get it all too well.

627
00:39:23,820 --> 00:39:25,113
I was in the same boat.

628
00:39:26,698 --> 00:39:28,116
Pride doesn't put food on the table.

629
00:39:28,909 --> 00:39:30,285
I don't know much about reporters,

630
00:39:30,368 --> 00:39:32,996
but something like this
would damage anyone's reputation

631
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:35,123
and make it hard down the line
when you switch jobs!

632
00:39:35,207 --> 00:39:37,459
Forget the political desk,
you'll just get fired!

633
00:39:37,542 --> 00:39:38,627
Even so, I refuse

634
00:39:38,710 --> 00:39:40,295
to apologize to that piece of trash.

635
00:39:42,464 --> 00:39:43,298
Fine.

636
00:39:43,882 --> 00:39:47,427
Having an extramarital affair
and fathering a child is wrong.

637
00:39:47,511 --> 00:39:50,055
But that daughter doesn't deserve this!

638
00:39:50,138 --> 00:39:51,598
You don't understand!

639
00:39:52,474 --> 00:39:53,350
That piece of trash…

640
00:39:54,893 --> 00:39:56,603
He's sexually harassed women for years!

641
00:39:59,147 --> 00:40:01,024
-Are you positive?
-Of course, I am!

642
00:40:01,108 --> 00:40:02,275
They told me in person.

643
00:40:02,359 --> 00:40:03,693
You know actor Yoon Jung-ho, right?

644
00:40:03,777 --> 00:40:05,821
He's a mature, charismatic actor
known for his strong acting.

645
00:40:05,904 --> 00:40:08,532
There are rumors going around
that he's dating a psychiatrist

646
00:40:08,615 --> 00:40:09,783
who is 30 years younger than him.

647
00:40:09,866 --> 00:40:11,034
Let's say that's true.

648
00:40:12,369 --> 00:40:13,203
But…

649
00:40:14,704 --> 00:40:16,998
dating a younger woman
isn't exactly a crime.

650
00:40:17,082 --> 00:40:18,667
Are you telling me
to make him look like trash?

651
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:19,918
It's okay if you do.

652
00:40:20,001 --> 00:40:21,920
Because he really is a piece of trash.

653
00:40:22,921 --> 00:40:24,840
Mr. Yoon, Se-na is here.

654
00:40:26,967 --> 00:40:28,051
Hello, sir.

655
00:40:30,887 --> 00:40:31,888
Hi, Se-na.

656
00:40:33,098 --> 00:40:34,766
Can you go over the lines with me?

657
00:40:35,267 --> 00:40:36,184
Yes, sir.

658
00:40:36,268 --> 00:40:37,352
Give us some privacy.

659
00:40:40,272 --> 00:40:41,857
-I wasn't the only one.
-Take a seat.

660
00:40:41,940 --> 00:40:44,484
He only went after those
in supporting or minor roles.

661
00:40:44,568 --> 00:40:46,945
The ones who had no power
or courage to stand up to him

662
00:40:47,821 --> 00:40:49,781
and were desperate for their next role.

663
00:40:54,703 --> 00:40:56,371
But you have power now.

664
00:40:56,454 --> 00:40:58,081
It's not too late to step up--

665
00:40:58,665 --> 00:40:59,708
Are you insane?

666
00:40:59,791 --> 00:41:03,503
You want me to risk my reputation
to take down a respected senior actor?

667
00:41:05,547 --> 00:41:07,174
Is there anyone else…

668
00:41:08,884 --> 00:41:09,926
who can prove this?

669
00:41:11,511 --> 00:41:13,305
What did the other victims say?

670
00:41:13,847 --> 00:41:14,764
They all declined, didn't they?

671
00:41:15,682 --> 00:41:16,725
They did.

672
00:41:16,808 --> 00:41:19,644
So if you could find the courage
to speak up--

673
00:41:19,728 --> 00:41:21,062
I don't want to find that kind of courage.

674
00:41:22,564 --> 00:41:25,442
I can't find that kind of courage,

675
00:41:25,942 --> 00:41:28,486
but I don't want to see him on TV anymore.

676
00:41:29,029 --> 00:41:32,407
I want to browse channels freely
without feeling uneasy.

677
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:34,534
The extent of his actions
is too terrible to put into words.

678
00:41:35,869 --> 00:41:37,204
I'll never apologize.

679
00:41:37,913 --> 00:41:39,748
-But…
-I can issue a correction on my article.

680
00:41:39,831 --> 00:41:42,167
But that's as far as I'll go.

681
00:41:42,792 --> 00:41:43,627
I…

682
00:42:04,940 --> 00:42:05,774
Thank you.

683
00:42:14,741 --> 00:42:17,285
Why are you making out
in front of my house?

684
00:42:17,786 --> 00:42:18,787
Get a motel room!

685
00:42:32,217 --> 00:42:33,134
How was it?

686
00:42:35,762 --> 00:42:36,763
My reflexes, I mean.

687
00:42:48,608 --> 00:42:49,693
By the way…

688
00:42:49,776 --> 00:42:50,860
I…

689
00:42:50,944 --> 00:42:53,863
I didn't get to finish
what I wanted to say.

690
00:42:56,616 --> 00:42:58,076
I'm a Hanguk University graduate!

691
00:42:58,159 --> 00:43:00,662
I can take care of myself, so don't worry.

692
00:43:04,541 --> 00:43:05,667
Jeez.

693
00:43:05,750 --> 00:43:07,085
"I'm a Hanguk University graduate!"

694
00:43:07,669 --> 00:43:08,795
Who said I was worried?

695
00:43:11,172 --> 00:43:12,090
Jeez.

696
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:26,730
Thank you for the ride.

697
00:43:27,564 --> 00:43:30,483
If you won't apologize,
then don't do anything at all.

698
00:43:30,567 --> 00:43:33,153
Don't write any more articles
and piss him off more.

699
00:43:33,236 --> 00:43:34,487
Please,

700
00:43:35,447 --> 00:43:36,865
just don't do anything.

701
00:43:36,948 --> 00:43:39,034
If I hadn't exposed the school corruption,

702
00:43:39,117 --> 00:43:41,369
I wouldn't have had to work part-time
to put myself through school.

703
00:43:41,453 --> 00:43:43,246
I could've just gotten a scholarship.

704
00:43:43,830 --> 00:43:46,583
I wouldn't have had to sacrifice
time and sleep to study,

705
00:43:46,666 --> 00:43:49,085
and I could've helped my brother
with his studies.

706
00:43:49,169 --> 00:43:51,296
And I might've even had time to date.

707
00:43:53,298 --> 00:43:54,674
But I have no regrets.

708
00:43:54,758 --> 00:43:57,469
If I could go back in time,
I'd do the same exact thing.

709
00:43:57,552 --> 00:43:58,803
I'd gladly take that loss

710
00:44:00,180 --> 00:44:01,306
on my own.

711
00:44:04,267 --> 00:44:05,101
Good night.

712
00:44:26,081 --> 00:44:26,915
"I'm…"

713
00:44:36,299 --> 00:44:37,175
WI JEONG-SIN

714
00:44:40,637 --> 00:44:42,389
WI JEONG-SIN

715
00:44:52,565 --> 00:44:53,441
Jeez.

716
00:44:55,151 --> 00:44:58,446
Why do our paths keep crossing?

717
00:44:59,114 --> 00:45:00,323
-Hey, Su-ji.
-Yes?

718
00:45:00,407 --> 00:45:02,492
I can't stop thinking about someone.

719
00:45:02,575 --> 00:45:05,745
Is there any way to make that stop?

720
00:45:05,829 --> 00:45:09,541
Whenever that person comes to mind,
replace them with a different thought.

721
00:45:09,624 --> 00:45:13,503
You can choose a good memory
or a different person.

722
00:45:34,065 --> 00:45:34,899
Onion!

723
00:45:43,867 --> 00:45:45,243
It rained a lot today.

724
00:45:45,326 --> 00:45:47,078
I hope you didn't get caught in it.

725
00:45:49,289 --> 00:45:51,958
Somebody gave me a ride home,
so I didn't get wet.

726
00:45:53,001 --> 00:45:54,085
Someone gave her a ride?

727
00:45:57,255 --> 00:45:58,339
Who?

728
00:45:58,423 --> 00:46:00,091
Did anything upsetting happen today?

729
00:46:01,301 --> 00:46:03,136
Of course, it did.

730
00:46:03,219 --> 00:46:06,764
There's this total jerk
who's been giving me a really hard time.

731
00:46:06,848 --> 00:46:08,600
I'll have to give them a piece of my mind.

732
00:46:09,726 --> 00:46:10,810
Please do.

733
00:46:11,478 --> 00:46:12,312
LOL

734
00:46:12,395 --> 00:46:14,439
I want to go somewhere
to take my mind off things,

735
00:46:14,522 --> 00:46:15,732
but I have no time.

736
00:46:17,192 --> 00:46:20,278
If you'd like, I can share
a simple feel-good method.

737
00:46:22,489 --> 00:46:23,990
I read in a book

738
00:46:24,073 --> 00:46:25,950
that giving compliments
for no reason can help.

739
00:46:26,743 --> 00:46:28,745
And when you see
the other person look pleased,

740
00:46:28,828 --> 00:46:30,330
it'll make you feel good too.

741
00:46:31,289 --> 00:46:32,749
I haven't tried it myself, though.

742
00:46:35,251 --> 00:46:36,503
Mr. Hwang.

743
00:46:38,880 --> 00:46:40,340
It wasn't me.

744
00:46:41,549 --> 00:46:44,761
Your outfit looks great today, Mr. Hwang.

745
00:46:47,263 --> 00:46:48,765
Right?

746
00:46:48,848 --> 00:46:51,476
I might not know much,
but I've got some fashion sense.

747
00:46:51,559 --> 00:46:53,394
I'm good with colors.

748
00:46:53,478 --> 00:46:56,314
Take a look at these shoes
and how they match my pants.

749
00:46:56,397 --> 00:46:59,192
Not everyone can pull off this look.

750
00:46:59,275 --> 00:47:01,194
It's a gift, I tell you.

751
00:47:01,277 --> 00:47:02,445
Hey, Gil-su.

752
00:47:02,529 --> 00:47:04,239
Stop the car for a moment.

753
00:47:04,989 --> 00:47:05,907
Sure.

754
00:47:05,990 --> 00:47:08,993
And this is one of my own
feel-good methods,

755
00:47:09,077 --> 00:47:10,370
and it costs nothing.

756
00:47:42,151 --> 00:47:45,863
Go outside on a sunny day
and simply stand there.

757
00:47:47,156 --> 00:47:48,074
That's it?

758
00:47:49,242 --> 00:47:50,827
After standing for a while,

759
00:47:51,661 --> 00:47:54,080
your head will start to feel warm
from the sunshine.

760
00:47:55,999 --> 00:47:57,417
When that happens,

761
00:47:58,251 --> 00:48:00,503
it feels like someone
is gently stroking your head.

762
00:48:01,879 --> 00:48:05,174
Nobody does that for you anymore
once you become an adult.

763
00:48:05,258 --> 00:48:07,176
So I like to think that my parents

764
00:48:07,260 --> 00:48:11,139
are the ones gently stroking my head.

765
00:48:12,724 --> 00:48:15,226
It makes me feel better.

766
00:48:21,733 --> 00:48:22,900
What's the matter with him?

767
00:48:25,236 --> 00:48:27,447
Is he not feeling well?

768
00:48:27,530 --> 00:48:29,449
He seems to be in some kind of pain.

769
00:48:38,207 --> 00:48:39,792
Oh, by the way,

770
00:48:39,876 --> 00:48:41,377
run and let yourself feel free.

771
00:48:42,170 --> 00:48:43,546
It'll totally clear your mind.

772
00:48:46,591 --> 00:48:47,550
Where's he going?

773
00:48:47,634 --> 00:48:48,551
What the heck?

774
00:48:51,512 --> 00:48:52,472
He's not okay.

775
